<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="699" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Buck</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-01-18"><hi rend="italic">January 18,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Buck reports that payment of taxes, even under protest, is still
                            refused by many Americans; that enforcement has been suspended until
                            January 25; and inquires whether he shall, having unofficially suggested
                            arbitration, also suggest it officially in the event that the
                            representatives of the other powers do so.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>